HEADWORD: Iridize
<hw>Ir"i*dize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Iridized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Iridizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To point or tip with iridium, as a gold
pen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make iridescent; <as>as, to <ex>iridize</ex>
glass</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iridoline</ent>⟦br⟧
